"confidentialité, authenticité, cyberdéfense, ANSSI, sécurité, "
"cybersécurité"

#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:20
msgid "Preamble and definitions"
msgstr "Préambule et définitions"

#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:24
msgid "The WAPT service operates as a **privileged** system account."
msgstr "Le service WAPT fonctionne en compte système **privilégié**."

#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:28

msgid ""
"From WAPT version 1.5, the default installation directory becomes "
":file:`C:\\\\Program Files (x86)\\\\wapt`."
msgstr ""
"A partir de la version 1.5 de WAPT, le répertoire d'installation par "
"défaut devient :file:`C:\\Program Files (x86)\\wapt`."

#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:33
msgid ""
"the sub-components :program:`wapttray`, :program:`waptservice` and "
":program:`waptexit` of the WAPT agent may be optionally deactivated "
"according to usage context."
msgstr ""
"Les sous-composantes :program:`wapttray`, :program:`waptservice` et "
":program:`waptexit` de l'agent WAPT peuvent être optionnellement "
"désactivées en fonction du contexte d'usage."

#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:38
msgid "Perimeter to secure"
msgstr "Périmètre à sécuriser"

#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:40
msgid "The elements to secure and that strictly concern WAPT are:"
msgstr "Les éléments à sécuriser qui concernent strictement WAPT sont :"

#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:42
msgid "**the WAPT Server** (*waptserver*);"
msgstr "**le serveur WAPT** (*waptserver*) ;"

#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:44
msgid ""
"**the WAPT agents** (*wapt-get*) and its sub-components (*wapttray*, "
"*waptservice* et *waptexit*);"
msgstr ""
"**les agents WAPT** (*wapt-get*) et ses sous-composantes (*wapttray*, "
"*waptservice* et *waptexit*) ;"

#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:47
msgid "**the management console** (*waptconsole*) ;"
msgstr "**la console de management** (*waptconsole*) ;"

#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:49
msgid "**the network communications** between these different components;"
msgstr "**les communications réseaux** entre ces différentes composantes ;"

#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:51
msgid ""
"In complement to the elements listed above, an :term:`Organization` that "
"uses WAPT will have to choose and follow a methodology that is adapted to"
" her use case:"
msgstr ""
"En complément des éléments listés ci-dessus, un exploitant de WAPT devra "
"choisir et suivre une méthodologie adaptée au contexte de son "
":term:`Organisation` pour :"

#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:55
msgid ""
"insure the safe provisioning of all other files that are to be "
"incorporated into a WAPT package;"
msgstr ""
"assurer un téléchargement sûr de tous les autres fichiers servant à "
"constituer un paquet WAPT ;"

#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:58
msgid ""
"develop the WAPT package python installation script so as to avoid any "
"exploitable security or confidentiality defect;"
msgstr ""
"rédiger le script python d'installation d'un paquet WAPT de telle manière"
" à éviter toute faille de sécurité ou de confidentialité exploitable ;"

#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:61
msgid "manage in a safe way the private keys for signing the packages;"
msgstr "gérer de manière sûre les clés privées de signature des paquets ;"

#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:63
msgid ""
"manage in a safe way the Autorities of Certification and Revocation for "
"the SSL and HTTPS certificates;"
msgstr ""
"gérer de manière sûre les Autorités de certification et de révocation des"
" certificats SSL et HTTPS ;"

#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:66
msgid ""
"The safe management of these complementary elements is excluded from the "
"perimeter of this documentation."
msgstr ""
"La gestion sûre de ces éléments complémentaires est exclue du périmètre "
"de cette documentation."

#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:70
msgid "Description of typical users"
msgstr "Description des utilisateurs typiques"

#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:72
msgid ""
"The following roles must be understood to evaluate the security "
"principles incorporated in WAPT:"
msgstr ""
"Les rôles suivants doivent être compris pour évaluer les principes de "
"sécurité présents dans WAPT :"

#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:75
msgid "**User**"
msgstr "**Utilisateur**"

#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:77
msgid ""
"individual/ user of a WAPT equipped end-device (**Enterprise** and "
"**Community**);"
msgstr ""
"individu / utilisateur d'une machine équipée de l'agent WAPT "
"(**Enterprise** et **Community**) ;"

#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:80
msgid "**Package Deployer**"
msgstr "**Déployeur de Paquets**"

#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:82
msgid ""
"individual with the ability to sign packages that **DO NOT** contain "
"python code (generally *group*, *host* and *unit* packages) and to upload"
" the package to the main repository (**Enterprise**);"
msgstr ""
"individu pouvant signer des paquets ne contenant pas de code python (en "
"général les paquets de type *group*, *unit* et *host*) et les charger sur"
" le dépôt principal (**Enterprise**) ;"

#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:86
msgid "**Package Developer**"
msgstr "**Développeur de Paquets**"

#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:88
msgid ""
"individual with the ability to sign any package, may it include or not "
"include python code, and to upload the package to the main repository "
"(**Enterprise**);"
msgstr ""
"individu pouvant signer des paquets, qu'ils intègrent ou non du code "
"python et les charger sur le dépôt principal (**Enterprise**) ;"

#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:92
msgid "**SuperAdmin**"
msgstr "**SuperAdmin**"

#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:94
msgid "all priviledged account in WAPT (**Community**);"
msgstr "compte unique ayant tous les droits dans WAPT (**Community**) ;"

#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:96
msgid "**Local Administrator**"
msgstr "**Administrateur Local**"

#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:98
msgid ""
"individual with local administration right of the WAPT equipped end-"
"devices (**Enterprise** and **Community**);"
msgstr ""
"utilisateur disposant des droits d'administration locaux sur les postes "
"équipés de WAPT (**Enterprise** et **Community**) ;"

#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:103
msgid ""
"Depending on the context within this documentation, an "
":term:`Administrator` will have the meaning of a :term:`Package "
"Deployer`, :term:`Package Developer` or :term:`SuperAdmin`."
msgstr ""
"En fonction du contexte de la documentation et de la version du produit, "
"un :term:`Administrateur` désignera un :term:`Déployeur de Paquets`, un "
":term:`Développeur de Paquets` ou bien le :term:`SuperAdmin`."

#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:109
msgid ""
"The :term:`Users` that are members of the Active Directory security group"
" **waptselfservice** are considered to be :term:`Local Administrators` "
"from the point of view of WAPT security."
msgstr ""
"Les :term:`Utilisateurs` membres du groupe de sécurité Active Directory "
"**waptselfservice** sont considérés comme des :term:`Administrateurs "
"Locaux` du point de vue de la sécurité WAPT."

#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:114
msgid "Description of the sensitive assets in WAPT"
msgstr "Description des biens sensibles"

#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:116
msgid ""
"By definition, a sensitive asset is a data (or a function) that is "
"considered as having value to an attacker."
msgstr ""
"Par définition, un bien sensible est une donnée (ou fonction) jugée comme"
" ayant de la valeur pour un attaquant."

#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:119
msgid ""
"Its value is estimated according to several security criteria (also "
"called security needs):"
msgstr ""
"Sa valeur est estimée selon des critères de sécurité (aussi appelés "
"besoins de sécurité) :"

#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:122
#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:174
msgid "availability;"
msgstr "disponibilité ;"

#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:124
#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:143
#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:160
#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:186
#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:201
#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:214
msgid "integrity;"
msgstr "intégrité ;"

#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:126
#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:145
#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:162
#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:188
#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:216
msgid "confidentiality;"
msgstr "confidentialité ;"

#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:128
#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:147
msgid "authenticity;"
msgstr "authenticité ;"

#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:130
msgid "The sensitive assets to protect are as follows:"
msgstr "Les biens sensibles à protéger sont les suivants :"

#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:133
msgid "Sensitive assets A1: communications"
msgstr "Bien sensible B1 : Les communications"

#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:135
msgid ""
"Communications between the central WAPT Server and the WAPT agents, as "
"well as the communications between the WAPT console and the WAPT Server "
"are a sensitive asset and they must be protected."
msgstr ""
"Les communications entre le serveur central et les agents ainsi que les "
"communications entre la console et le serveur sont un bien sensible et "
"doivent être protégées."

#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:141
msgid "Need for securing the communications"
msgstr "Besoin de sécurité des communications :"

#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:150
msgid "Sensitive asset A2: inventory data"
msgstr "Bien sensible B2 : Les données d'inventaire"

#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:152
msgid ""
"The informations on the state of deployment of the packages, as well as "
"hardware and software configurations of the end-devices are a sensitive "
"asset and they must be protected."
msgstr ""
"Les informations sur l'état de déploiement des paquets, ainsi que "
"configuration matérielle et logicielle des postes clients sont un bien "
"sensible et doivent être protégées."

#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:158
msgid "Security need of the inventory data"
msgstr "Besoin de sécurité des données d'inventaire :"

#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:165
msgid "Sensitive asset A3: log journals"
msgstr "Bien sensible B3 : Les journaux d'historique"

#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:167
msgid ""
"The logs generated by WAPT on the central server and by the agents are a "
"sensitive asset and they must be protected."
msgstr ""
"Les journaux générés par WAPT sur le serveur central et les agents sont "
"un bien sensible et doivent être protégés."

#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:172
msgid "Security needs of historical logs"
msgstr "Besoin de sécurité des journaux d'historique"

#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:177
msgid "Sensitive asset A4: configuration values"
msgstr "Bien sensible B4 : Les valeurs de configuration"

#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:179
msgid ""
"The configuration values (HTTPS server keys, database access "
"configuration, server authentication configuration) are sensitive and "
"they must be protected."
msgstr ""
"Les valeurs de configuration du serveur (clés du serveur https, "
"configuration accès à la base de données, configuration de "
"l'authentification au serveur) sont un bien sensible et doivent être "
"protégés."

#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:184
#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:199
msgid "Security needs of configuration values"
msgstr "Besoin de sécurité des valeurs de configuration :"

#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:191
msgid "Sensitive asset A5: WAPT executables on the end-devices"
msgstr "Bien sensible B5 : Les exécutables WAPT installés sur les postes client"

#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:193
msgid ""
"The WAPT executables installed on managed clients are a sensitive asset "
"and they must be protected (i.e. the content of the :file:`<WAPT>` "
"directory that includes the binaries, the configuration files and the "
"local database)."
msgstr ""
"Les exécutables WAPT installés sur les postes client managés (contenu du "
"répertoire wapt incluant les binaires, les dll, les fichiers de "
"configuration et la base de données) sont un bien sensible et doivent "
"être protégés."

#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:204
msgid "Sensitive asset A6: authentication"
msgstr "Bien sensible B6 : L'authentification"

#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:206
msgid ""
"Authentication to the administration console as well as the "
"authentication of the clients on the WAPT Server are a sensitive asset "
"and they must be protected (public key of each WAPT agent)."
msgstr ""
"Les données d'authentification à la console d'administration ainsi que "
"les données d'authentification des agents sur le serveur (clé publique de"
" chaque agent WAPT) sont un bien sensible et doivent être protégées."

#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:212
msgid "Security need of the authentication"
msgstr "Besoin de sécurité de l'authentification :"

#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:219
msgid "Description of hypotheses on WAPT's working environment"
msgstr "Description des hypothèses sur l'environment d'exploitation de WAPT"

#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:221
msgid ""
"By definition, the hypotheses are statements on WAPT's usage context or "
"its working environment."
msgstr ""
"Par définition, les hypothèses sont des déclarations portant sur le "
"contexte d'emploi de WAPT ou de son environment."

#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:224
msgid "The following hypotheses on WAPT's working environment must be considered:"
msgstr ""
"Les hypothèses suivantes sur l'environment d'exploitation de WAPT doivent"
" être considérées :"

#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:227
msgid "Hypothesis H1: the Administrators and the Package Deployers are trained"
msgstr ""
"Hypothèse H1 : Les Administrateurs et Gestionnaires de Déploiement WAPT "
"sont formés"

#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:229
msgid ""
"The :term:`Administrators` and the :term:`Package Deployers` are trained "
"on WAPT usage. In particular, they must insure that their logins, "
"passwords and private keys are kept secret."
msgstr ""
"Les :term:`Administrateurs` et les :term:`Déployeurs de paquets` sont "
"formés à l'usage de WAPT. En particulier, ils doivent s'assurer que leurs"
" identifiants et clés de sécurité restent secrets."

#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:234
msgid "Hypothesis H2: the operating systems underlying WAPT are sane"
msgstr "Hypothèse H2 : Les systèmes subjacents à WAPT sont sains"

#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:236
msgid ""
"WAPT's underlying operating systems implement adequate protection "
"mechanisms that are configured according to good practice (confinement, "
"access control, etc)."
msgstr ""
"Les systèmes d'exploitation sur lesquels les agents WAPT s'exécutent "
"mettent en oeuvre des mécanismes de protection adéquats (confinement, "
"contrôle d'accès, etc.) paramétrés et configurés selon les bonnes "
"pratiques."

#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:240
msgid ""
"The underlying operating system are patched and up to date at the time of"
" the installation of WAPT, they are free of viruses, trojan horses, etc."
msgstr ""
"Les systèmes d'exploitation sont à jour des correctifs en vigueur au "
"moment de l'installation, ils sont sains et exempts de virus, chevaux de "
"Troie, etc."

#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:244
msgid "Hypothesis H3: the binaries necessary for WAPT to operate are sane"
msgstr ""
"Hypothèse H3 : Les binaires nécessaires au fonctionnement de WAPT sont "
"intègres"

#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:246
msgid ""
"All libraries and tools necessary to install WAPT are considered to be "
"sane. Upon the WAPT agent receiving a request, the agent verifies that "
"the request has been properly signed."
msgstr ""
"Toutes les librairies et outils nécessaires au fonctionnement de WAPT "
"sont considérées saines. A la réception d'une requête par l'agent WAPT, "
"il vérifie que la requête est correctement signée ;"

#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:251
msgid "Hypothesis H4: the WAPT packages are built in a safe manner"
msgstr "Hypothèse H4 : Les paquets WAPT sont construits de manière sûre"

#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:253
msgid ""
"The :term:`Administrator` is responsible for insuring that the files to "
"be incorporated into a WAPT package come from safe sources and are free "
"of viruses, trojan horses, etc."
msgstr ""
"Il est de la responsabilité de l':term:`Administrateur` de s'assurer que "
"les fichiers destinés à être intégrés dans des paquets WAPT proviennent "
"de sources sûres et sont en particuliers exempts de virus, chevaux de "
"Troie, etc."

#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:258
msgid "Hypothesis H5: the Users of the end-devices are not Local Administrators"
msgstr ""
"Hypothèse H5 : Les Utilisateurs des postes client ne sont pas "
"Administrateurs Locaux"

#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:260
msgid ""
"A :term:`User` must not have local administration rights on the WAPT "
"equipped device. Otherwise, the :term:`User` must be considered a "
":term:`Local Administrator`."
msgstr ""
"Un :term:`Utilisateur` n'a pas les droits d'administration de son poste "
"de travail. Sinon l':term:`Utilisateur` est considéré comme un "
":term:`Administrateur Local`."

#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:264
msgid ""
"In particular, a :term:`User` must not have write access to WAPT's "
"installation directory."
msgstr ""
"En particulier, l':term:`Utilisateur` n'a pas les droits d'écriture dans "
"le répertoire d'installation du client WAPT."

#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:268
msgid "Hypothesis H6: the Local Administrators are trained"
msgstr "Hypothèse H6 : Les Administrateurs Locaux des postes client sont formés"

#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:270
msgid ""
"The :term:`Local Administrator` of a device must be trained to use WAPT, "
"or at minimum he must not make changes to files located in WAPT's "
"installation folder."
msgstr ""
"L':term:`Administrateur Local` d'un poste client doit être formé à "
"l'exploitation de WAPT, ou à défaut ne pas modifier les fichiers "
"d'installation se trouvant dans le dossier d'installation de WAPT."

#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:275
msgid "Description of threats on WAPT's sensitive assets"
msgstr "Description des menaces pesant sur les biens sensibles WAPT"

#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:277
msgid ""
"By definition, a threat is an action or an event susceptible to bring "
"prejudice to the security of the WAPT equipped device."
msgstr ""
"Par définition, une menace est une action ou un événement susceptible de "
"porter préjudice à la sécurité globale de la machine équipée de WAPT."

#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:280
msgid ""
"The threat agents to be considered for evaluating security in WAPT are as"
" follows:"
msgstr ""
"Les agents menaçants à considérer pour l'évaluation de sécurité sont les "
"suivants :"

#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:283
msgid ""
"**Unauthorized entities**: it is a human attacker or en entity that "
"interacts with WAPT without legitimately having access to it."
msgstr ""
"**Entités non-autorisées** : il s'agit d'un attaquant humain ou d'une "
"entité qui interagit avec WAPT mais qui ne dispose pas d'un accès "
"légitime à celui-ci."

#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:288
msgid ""
"The :term:`Administrators` and the :term:`Local Administrators` are not "
"considered to be attackers."
msgstr ""
"Les :term:`Administrateurs` et les :term:`Administrateurs Locaux` ne sont"
" pas considérés comme des attaquants."

#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:291
msgid ""
"The threats bearing on WAPT's sensitive assets defined above are as "
"follow:"
msgstr ""
"Les menaces qui portent sur les biens sensibles WAPT définis ci-dessus "
"sont les suivantes :"

#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:294
msgid "Threat T1: installation of an unsafe software by an unauthorized entity"
msgstr ""
"Menace M1 : Installation d'un logiciel malveillant par une entité non-"
"autorisée"

#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:296
msgid ""
"This threat corresponds to an attacker that would be able to use a "
"component of the WAPT agent to permanently install a malicious "
"application, or to remove or deactivate a security component on the WAPT "
"equipped device."
msgstr ""
"Cette menace correspond à un attaquant qui parviendrait à utiliser une "
"composante de l'agent WAPT pour installer une application malveillante de"
" façon pérenne, ou pour désinstaller ou désactiver une composante de "
"sécurité du poste sur lequel l'agent WAPT est installé."

#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:301
msgid "Threat T2: modification of configuration values by an unauthorized entity"
msgstr ""
"Menace M2 : Altération de valeurs de configuration par une entité non-"
"autorisée"

#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:303
msgid ""
"The threat corresponds to an attacker that would be able to modify a "
"configuration element of WAPT that had been previously defined by a "
"legitimate WAPT :term:`Administrator`."
msgstr ""
"Cette menace correspond à un attaquant qui parviendrait à modifier ou à "
"supprimer le paramétrage d'un élément de WAPT défini par un "
":term:`Administrateur` légitime de WAPT."

#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:308
msgid "Threat T3: illegitimate access by an unauthorized entity"
msgstr "Menace M3 : Accès illégitime par une entité non-autorisée"

#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:310
msgid ""
"This threat corresponds to an attacker that would be able to recover the "
"login credentials of an :term:`Administrator`, or bypass the "
"authentication mechanism in such a way to access or alter a sensitive "
"asset stored on the server. It also corresponds to an attacker being able"
" to impersonate a WAPT agent."
msgstr ""
"Cette menace correspond à un attaquant qui parviendrait à récupérer les "
"données d'authentification d'un :term:`Administrateur`, à contourner le "
"mécanisme d'authentification de manière à accéder ou à altérer un bien "
"sensible stocké sur le serveur. Elle correspond également à un attaquant "
"qui parviendrait à se faire passer pour un agent WAPT."

#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:317
msgid "Threat T4: network listening by an unauthorized entity"
msgstr "Menace M4 : Écoute du réseau par une entité non-autorisée"

#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:319
msgid ""
"This threat corresponds to an attacker being able to intercept and gain "
"knowledge of network traffic between the WAPT agents and the server "
"hosting WAPT."
msgstr ""
"Cette menace correspond à un attaquant qui parviendrait à intercepter et "
"prendre connaissance des communications réseaux entre les agents et le "
"serveur hébergeant WAPT."

#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:324
msgid ""
"Threat T5: modification of network traffic by an unauthorized entity "
"(type *Man In The Middle*)"
msgstr ""
"Menace M5 : Altération du trafic réseau par une entité non-autorisée "
"(Type *Man In the Middle*)"

#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:326
msgid ""
"This threat corresponds to an attacker being able to alter network "
"traffic between the agents and the server hosting WAPT, or between the "
"console and the WAPT Server."
msgstr ""
"Cette menace correspond à un attaquant qui parviendrait à modifier les "
"communications réseaux entre les agents et le serveur hébergeant WAPT ou "
"les communications réseau entre la console et le serveur WAPT."

#: ../../source/wapt-security-principles/safety-principle.rst:331
